strings.Value: "You did your duty by warning me, and I'm grateful. I'll set off to find them immediately."
"Where do you think they may have gone?"
"Hmm... what if they got into a battle without me. Can't let them have all the fun — let's go find them."
"They can fall into Rovagug's jaws for all I care. Get out of here!"
"They will have to deal with it themselves, I can't leave my responsibilities here to chase Ekun."
{n}Elina's face is pale, and her red hair is a mess.{/n} "It's awful, Your Grace! Ekun is missing, and {d|Ntavi}Ntavi{/d} too!"

"He was happy for a while after our fest. Things were going well... but then he started feeling down — restless. His thoughts may have turned to his family again. And then this... {d|Ntavi}Ntavi{/d} kept turning up."
{n}Elina looks surprised.{/n} "A-As Your Grace wishes... thank you!"

"If only we knew for sure, Your Grace! There is one spot though — a bridge over the {g|Gudrin River}Gudrin River{/g}... travelers have gone missing there, they say it might be the work of giants. Ntavi was close when some woodcutter told me about it. And I'm thinking, maybe this woman dragged Ekun there?"

"And the more he talked to Ntavi, the worse he got. She was whispering something in his ear, and he kept ordering more and more wine... then last night they left the inn, armed to the teeth! I tried to stop them, but I couldn't... they haven't been back since!"
"In {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}'s name, Your Grace, please find Ekun! My heart says this won't end well."
{n}Elina looks at you, terrified.{/n} "F-Forgive me, Your Grace... I'm leaving..."
"I... I see, Your Grace. Oh, I hope nothing bad happened to them..."
